        <td bgcolor="#DbDdB3" colspan="2" valign="top"><img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;07/12/2001&nbsp;:&nbsp; 9:09:51 PM</font>

        
		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=26"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=26')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_messengers.asp?mode=ICQ&ICQ=1984232&M_NAME=Borlanis')"><img src="http://online.mirabilis.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=1984232&img=5" height=15 width=15 alt="Send Borlanis an ICQ Message" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=1231&FORUM_ID=19&CAT_ID=8&Forum_Title=Tales+and+Stories+of+Adventure&Topic_Title=Adventure+of+a+Lifetime+part+3"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Borlanis  was one step away, but it was a step of epic proportions.  A full scale raid on the City of Mist, and the killing of two of the most fierce creatures on the continent was needed.   Hesitatingly the call for aid went out.  His close friends volunteered immediatly but so many more were needed.</P><P>And then an amazing thing happened.  It started with a trickle and grew and grew.  First one, then two, then six and the Amber Order soon filled the halls of the City of Mist!</P><P>Madasra agreed to shoulder the responsiblilty of leading this raid and Sekul and Judice arrange the forces.  Soon there were four strong groups ready to take on the macbre denisons of that foul zone.  Over 20 heroes were there that night.  It brought a tear to my one eye for they were there for me, for I am Borlanis, the barbarian.</P><P>Boldly and proudly we marched into the zone.  Before long we came to the castle and the lock was picked by the skillful Castilla. As we continued onward with Judice pulling the mobs and our tanks led by the pally Norgaard and casters doing indescribable amounts of damage.  The shouts of "Big Bang" by Shahx were oftem the last thing heard by many a creature.</P><P>We fought our way to the top without incident and made the room where the Vile Neh'Ashiir was said to roam.  And we did not wait in vain.  Upon my giving of the ring, Neh'Ashiir showed his true colors and attacked.  A mighty battle followed but the outcome was never in doubt.  The foul ghost fell and upon inspection a diary was found.  I knew that the spirit of the lake would need to see this so the druid Kuldaen offered up to take me to that land where I could find the spirit.  Little did he know that kind gesture would later extract a large payment.  </P><P>The spirit was indeed interested in the book and sent me back to speak with another undead of the caste, the daunting Lord Rak'Ashiir.  As we worked out way back down from the top floor we had our first casualty.  The good druid Moil had apparantly drawn the wrath of the inhabitants of the first house and layed down his life in battle.  Our clerics, worked their magic and once again the noble Moil was among us.  Our forces continued downward.  In a hallway we waited as Norgaard and Castilla worked hand in hand, bringing us mob after mob.  We fought hard and well, and then the unthinkable happened.  Norgaard was there, and then he wasn't. His life snuffed out by a black reaver.  That reaver, assisted by another made our camp and a great battle ensued.  Pets died, comrads died, but it looked to be a salvagable battle when Castilla backstabbed the reaver and it fell to its death.  Then it happened.  Our doom.  Lord Rak'Ashiir appeared on the scene and something must not have been to his liking for a great fire fell from the sky wiping out member after member of our once proud group.  Soon there were none left.  And that wasnt the worst of it for myself and poor Kuldaen.  We had both made the hallway our home points and upon our deaths found ourselves dying again and again to these foul mobs.  If a druid in wolf form has 9 lives, Kuldaen used up half or them.  And who was I to let him go it alone and joined him in many deaths?</P><P>to be continued...</font></td>
      </tr>

